Crumble @ground beef{3%lbs} into a #large pot{} or Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring frequently until evenly browned.  Drain off grease.  
Add @chopped onion{1%cup} and @chopped celery{1%cup}, and cook until the onion is tender, about 3 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium and pour in @chili sauce{12%oz} (one 12 oz. bottle of tomato-based chili sauce).  Stir in @apple cider vinegar{1/4%cup} and @sugar{1/4%cup}.  Add @mustard{1%tsp} if using.  Simmer until the mixture is your desired thickness.  Serve on buns.